thread.title_full: Dabo Swinney calls FSU's Dalvin Cook best RB in country

author: Andrew Holleran
title: Dabo Swinney calls FSU's Dalvin Cook best RB in country
text:
Dabo Swinney calls FSU's Dalvin Cook best RB in country College Spun 1 day ago Andrew Holleran © Melina Vastola-USA TODAY Sports Clemson head coach Dabo Swinney had high praise for Florida State Seminoles running back Dalvin Cook. There might not be a position in college football more loaded with talent than running back.
AdChoices There’s LSU’s Leonard Fournette, Ohio State’s Ezekiel Elliott, Utah’s Devontae Booker, Alabama’s Derrick Henry and many other elite players at the position.
Who’s the best? According to Clemson’s Dabo Swinney, it’s Florida State’s Dalvin Cook.
Swinney says Florida State's Dalvin Cook is the "best running back in the country."
— Brad Senkiw (@BradSenkiw_AIM) October 20, 2015
Dabo Swinney asked about Dalvin Cook vs. Leonard Fournette: "They're both really good, but you can only pick one, I'm picking Dalvin Cook."
— Dan Hope (@Dan_Hope) October 20, 2015
Most would give that title to Fournette, this season’s Heisman Trophy front-runner and a potential future top-five pick in an NFL Draft.
Cook is having quite a year, too, though. The sophomore has totaled 955 yards and 10 touchdowns this season, averaging 8.7 yards a carry.
FSU and Clemson are set to play Nov. 7.
